2. Components Required
-Arduino Uno
-3 LEDs
-3 × 220Ω Resistors
-Breadboard
-Connecting wires
3.code--
int led1 = 2;
int led2 = 3;
int led3 = 4;

unsigned long time1 = 0;
unsigned long time2 = 0;
unsigned long time3 = 0;

int state1 = 0;
int state2 = 0;
int state3 = 0;

void setup()
{
    pinMode(led1, OUTPUT);
    pinMode(led2, OUTPUT);
    pinMode(led3, OUTPUT);
}

void loop()
{
    unsigned long current = millis();

    // LED1 → 500 ms
    if (current - time1 >= 500)
    {
        time1 = current;
        state1 = !state1;
        digitalWrite(led1, state1);
    }

    // LED2 → 1000 ms
    if (current - time2 >= 1000)
    {
        time2 = current;
        state2 = !state2;
        digitalWrite(led2, state2);
    }

    // LED3 → 1500 ms
    if (current - time3 >= 1500)
    {
        time3 = current;
        state3 = !state3;
        digitalWrite(led3, state3);
    }
}
4. working--
Three LEDs blink at different speeds using the Arduino.
millis() is used so all LEDs blink at the same time without delay.
